  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-ON-02 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. This synthetic adversarial sample targets W-ON-02: the ContextOfUse description enumerates operating ranges in prose (temperature 37 °C ± 1 °C, inlet pressure 5–15 mmHg, flow rates 2–8 L/min, rotational speeds 2400–3600 RPM, turbulent regime Re 4000–12000) but no hasApplicabilityConstraint or hasOperatingEnvelope link is emitted, leaving the model's formal range of valid use unspecified.",
