    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Assessment team accepted the credibility package for submission on the basis that all 13 factors have been formally evaluated and the Monte Carlo UQ results demonstrate hemolysis below clinical threshold at 4 of 5 operating points. Achieved levels below required levels across all factors are acknowledged; the package is accepted as a complete characterization of current evidence gaps rather than as a demonstration of sufficient credibility. Regulatory submission will include this gap analysis as the basis for requesting conditional approval with post-market hemolysis monitoring. Note: the operating envelope and applicability constraints are described in prose within the COU description but have not been formally encoded as machine-readable constraints, which may limit automated scope-checking against future model reuse scenarios.",
